@NODE Introduction "Introduction"
Introduction:

    Because  there  is  no  pgp-support  for  UMS available yet, I've
    written  this  small  script  to  make it easy to handle received
    pgp-mails.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Howdoesitwork "How does it work?"
How does it work?

    Joe  receives  one  or more pgp-mails. These mails must be <new>!
    UMSpgp  will  detect  these  mails,  asks  for your pgp-password,
    decrypts these mails and Postmaster will send the decrypted mails
    to Joe. The pgp-mails-status will be set to <old>.

    Another  mail  would  be  created and send from Postmaster to Joe
    which contains some information about this procedure.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Contents "Contents"
Contents:

    The archive must contain the following files:

    Directory of ums:pgp
    -------rw-d 21:50:00 08-Dez-94 60001 60000        1370 info_main
    -------rw-d 21:50:00 08-Dez-94 60001 60000         617 pgp_from_txt.mfm
    -------rw-d 21:50:00 08-Dez-94 60001 60000          10 pgp_msg_txt.mfm
    -------rw-d 21:50:00 08-Dez-94 60001 60000         152 script_main
    ----s--rwed 21:50:00 08-Dez-94 60001 60000          94 umspgp
    -------rw-d 22:06:08 08-Dez-94 60001 60000        4066 umspgp.doc
    -------rw-d 22:02:54 08-Dez-94 60001 60000         533 umspgp.doc.info
    -------rw-d 22:06:28 08-Dez-94 60001 60000        4641 umspgp.guide
    -------rw-d 22:02:54 08-Dez-94 60001 60000         517 umspgp.guide.info
    -------rw-d 22:02:54 08-Dez-94 60001 60000        1633 umspgp.info
    ----s--rwed 21:50:00 08-Dez-94 60001 60000        1783 umspgpcheck
     49 Blocks, 15,492 Bytes used in 11 files

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "Installation"
Installation:

    Two  users  are  recommended  to  use this script: one user, e.g.
    'Joe' (yourself) and a second user e.g. Postmaster or Sysop.

    Just  extract  the  archive  to  ums:.  A  new  directory will be
    created, where the above mentioned files would be copied to.

    That's it. (no more 'search & replace'-actions yet ;-) )!
@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "Usage"
Usage:

    From Shell:

    umspgpcheck <user> <passwd> <postmaster> <p's passwd> <server>

    The  mails  which  <user> has received, will be checked. If there
    there  are pgp-mails, then they will be decrypted and <user> will
    receive the decrypted one from <postmaster>.


    From Workbench:

    There is another file called 'ums_pgp'. Edit this file and insert
    your  favorite  usernames  and  passwords.  Then you have only to
    double-click these icon.
@ENDNODE

